.TH "devm_spi_mem_dirmap_create" 9 "devm_spi_mem_dirmap_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_spi_mem_dirmap_create \- Create a direct mapping descriptor and attach it to a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct spi_mem_dirmap_desc *" devm_spi_mem_dirmap_create
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct spi_mem *mem "  ","
.BI "const struct spi_mem_dirmap_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device the dirmap desc will be attached to
.IP "mem" 12
SPI mem device this direct mapping should be created for
.IP "info" 12
direct mapping information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
devm_ variant of the \fBspi_mem_dirmap_create\fP function. See
\fBspi_mem_dirmap_create\fP for more details.
.SH "RETURN"
a valid pointer in case of success, and \fBERR_PTR\fP otherwise.
